section.section:
"Expert child abuse or neglect care" means the diagnosis or treatment of child abuse or neglect provided by:
a physician;
a multidisciplinary team or multidisciplinary team member;
a health care facility; or
a staff member of a health care facility who is an expert in the field of abuse and neglect.

text.section:
Any provider who is licensed or authorized to practice a profession in this State shall examine or treat any child, with or without the consent of the child's parent, guardian, or custodian, to determine the nature and extent of any abuse or neglect to the child if the child is brought to the provider:
in accordance with a juvenile court order;
by a representative of a local department of social services who states that the representative believes the child is an abused or neglected child;
by a police officer who states that the officer believes that the child is an abused or neglected child; or
by an individual required under § 5-704 of this subtitle to report suspected child abuse or neglect.
